WRITING.TEXT: I #8217;ve always had emotional eating and binging issues. A crummy day or someone making fun of me would always end up in me tearfully cramming anything I could find into my mouth. My parents would have to hide the chocolate chips when I ran out of my own sugary foods. We had many arguments about how I would eat half of a jar of high-end cherry jam, just to get that little serotonin rush. Although I kept thinking #8220;Frick it, I don #8217;t care about myself, nothing matters, Ill just keep eating #8221;- it adds up. And I DID care about myself and how I looked. A lot. Which made me feel worse, and the cycle continues. After eating healthily for a few consecutive weeks and working out daily, the most satisfying thing is to look into my fridge, see all kinds of delicious foods, and be able to walk away- somehow, without a craving. Without feeling the impulse to eat as much as I can of it before my parents see. I #8217;ve learned better ways to deal with my emotions, and I am changing as an entire person!
